    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1367"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1367">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/598a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Brown Brothers &amp; Co. and J. &amp; W. Seligman &amp;
                            Co</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department will be glad to have you place two hundred of the four hundred
                    thousand of Nicaragua’s money at their disposal. Immediately a telegraphic reply
                    comes from Nicaragua, you will be advised regarding the arrangement respecting
                    the balance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
